OL,3,CWho are the people in the asylum
OL,4,Cbacklog that the government is
OL,5,Cclearing?
OL,7,F"During that time, we've been so
OL,8,Fconcerned and it's really
OL,9,Fheartbreaking to see people stuck in
OL,10,Fthose hotels, week after week, month
OL,11,Fafter month, especially seeing
OL,12,Ffamilies living in hotel rooms," said
OL,13,FBen Gilchrist, CEO of Caritas
OL,14,FShrewsbury.
OL,16,F"The particular problems that we see
OL,17,Fdirectly is the mental health and
OL,18,Fwellbeing impacts on people, they're
OL,19,Fstuck in doors a lot of the time.
